OL,3,CCouncil defends contractors wearing
OL,4,Cbalaclavas to remove flags from
OL,5,Clampposts
OL,7,F"That's because previous and current
OL,8,Fcontractors and council staff have
OL,9,Fbeen seriously threatened - in person
OL,10,Fand online - so this is a necessary
OL,11,Fmeasure to allow them to undertake
OL,12,Ftheir work safely.
OL,14,F"The council is aware of the
OL,15,Fcoordination of serious organised
OL,16,Fharassment and intimidation, and
OL,17,Fthreats towards its contractor, which
OL,18,Fmeans anonymity is essential.
